column10: descripcion:"A key secondary objective for the study was added with the key secondary endpoint of “Response based on an absolute SALT Score ≤10 at Week 24”. This key secondary endpoint will be analyzed utilizing an appropriate testing procedure to control overall Type I error. This change applies to the overall study; therefore
column11: it does not change the primary and key secondary\nobjectives and endpoints for the European Medicines Agency (EMA)
column12:
which are different than those for the overall study and remain the same as the one from previous version of the
protocol.
Clarification was added regarding the key secondary endpoint of “PGI-C response defined as a score of “moderately improved” or “greatly improved” at Week 24” for the EMA and competent authorities in the Voluntary Harmonisation Procedure (VHP) countries. The testing procedures for multiple comparisons were revised to align with the reorganization of the endpoints for the
study. The analyses of the primary and key secondary endpoints were revised to separate those analyses to be performed for the overall study and for specific regulatory regions in order to
address differences in advise received from some regulatory agencies."

dated 06 December 2018
Revised secondary and exploratory objectives and endpoints.
Revised sample size based on the ongoing blinded review of pooled primary CDI events resulting in increasing the planned enrollment by approximately 1700 additional subjects.
Additionally:
• Refined the parameters included in healthcare resource utilization score
• mITT-1 population has been defined
• Editorial updates to the Data Analysis/Statistical Methods 
• Incorporated protocol administrative change to medical device complaint reporting procedure
• Incorporated protocol administrative change to clarify visit 6 can be conducted in person
• Incorporated France- and Japan-specific appendices"

31 Oct 2019
Objectives and endpoint table: Primary estimand edited for clarity and secondary endpoint criteria sub-divided in to “key secondary” and “other secondary”.
Health related quality of life estimands and endpoint were incorrectly outlined as “total domain score”. These have been updated to “individual domain scores”
Added details of all planned adjudication committees. 
Section 1.3. Schedule of activities
Footnote x added to specify that direct coombs should only be sent to a local laboratory only if the investigator suspects a clinically significant hemolytic anemia that will be scored on the BILAG and added to Appendix 12.
eGFR cystatin added at all visits. Urine microscopic exam added at all visits.
ECG assessment added at Week 2 so as to assess cardiac function in combination with detailed PK assessments
Whole blood PBMC assessment in now an optional sample and has been moved to banked biospecimen section of SOA.
SLICC criteria added to make the SOA assessments consistent with the Inclusion Criteria. 
MMF language updated removing the criteria for assessment to be performed at 12 hrs ± 30 mins.
Participants are instead asked to refrain from taking a dose immediately prior to clinic visits where MMF levels are assessed.
Section 5.1. Inclusion criteria and Section 5.2. Exclusion criteria were reviewed some were updated.
Section 5.4. Clarifications for rescreening added."

column10: descripcion:"Estudio DINAMOTM (estudio principal)\nSe planifica realizar el estudio en niños y adolescentes tratados con dieta y ejercicio y con tratamiento de base con metformina y/o insulina. Los pacientes que no toleran la metformina y que son tratados con dieta y ejercicio solamente tienen una necesidad médica insatisfecha de fármacos antidiabéticos orales que no sean la metformina
column11:
y se espera que se beneficien enormemente de la participación en este estudio.

Estudio DINAMOTM Mono:
El Estudio TODAY ha mostrado que la mayoría de los jóvenes con T2DM pueden ser tratados eficazmente con monoterapia con metformina durante los primeros 12 meses de la enfermedad. Sin embargo
column12: el Estudio TODAY también demostró que la monoterapia con metformina no logra mantener un nivel de HbA1c <8
column13: 0 % en la mayoría de los adolescentes durante el segundo año de tratamiento
column14: incluso en caso de niveles sustanciales de insulina residual endógena. Por lo tanto
column15: se justifica la realización de estudios para evaluar si los medicamentos antidiabéticos orales pueden reemplazar a la metformina como terapia inicial o bien si el paciente puede ser transferido de la monoterapia con metformina. en caso de fracaso de la metformina
column17: en lugar de iniciar la terapia con insulina.\n"

paragraph 1. Duplicate text referencing the use of rescue medication has been removed.
Section 7.2 Patient discontinuation/ withdrawal from study: The following wording was removed so as to clarify participants right to withdraw: Participants should be questioned regarding their reason for withdrawal.
Section 7.2 Withdrawal of consent: Wording regarding the need for participants to notify the investigator in writing of the decision to withdraw consent removed so as to clarify participants right to withdraw.
Section 8.1.9 Joint Assessments. Reference to medical marijuana removed and reference to narcotics replaced with lower potency opioid analgesics to make it consistent with Appendix 13.
Section 8.2.3 Vital Signs
column20: reference to tympanic assessment of body temperature removed as assessment instruments for SLE require an oral temperature.\nSection 9.5.1 Data Monitoring Committee. The section has been updated to outline that the external data monitoring committee (E-DMC) is a sponsor\nAppendix 2
column21: Table 4: References to Pneumococcal and tetanus antibodies have been removed as these are not assessed in this protocol.\nSection 10.4.4
column22: Appendix 4: Contraceptive Methods. Section heading re-instated as missing from prior version. Only highly effective methods are permitted per protocol as such the following contraceptive methods defined as “effective methods” have been removed."

descripcion:"PA4 dated 28 Sep 2020.
Added the definition of an outpatient visit to inclusion criterion 4.
Clarified systemic antibiotic use for the purposes of inclusion criterion 4.
Added a reminder every 2 weeks for all subjects to collect a stool sample should a diarrheal episode occur.
Clarified the requirement to capture major protocol deviations."

column10: descripcion:"To align with newly published literature (Wyrwich et al
column11: 2020) and new feedback from clinical experts in alopecia areata that SALT ≤20 best distinguishes treatment success from lack of success
column12: from the perspective of both clinicians and patients. These changes have been made after consultation with a regulatory agency."

column10: descripcion:"This was previously included in the protocol (to use either SALT ≤10 or ≤20 for the primary objective and endpoint based on regulatory feedback); however
column11: this language has been added\nto align with a regulatory agency request to specify that SALT ≤10 will be used in the EU.\nThe original footnote “a” was no longer necessary following these changes; the list of VHP countries was added for reference instead."

column15: descripcion:"To align with a request from the VHP to require male subjects in VHP countries in the EU to use a barrier method of contraception during heterosexual intercourse and to refrain from donating sperm during the relevant period. Update the definition of “postmenopausal state”."
